# Shared Field Resolver (`lib/field-resolver.ts`)

All field value resolution, insured name extraction, and template formatting MUST use the shared module.

## When to use

| Need | Import from `@/lib/field-resolver` |
|------|-----|
| Resolve a field value from snapshot by source + key | `resolveRawValue(ref, ctx)` |
| Resolve + format in one call (PDF/HTML templates) | `resolveAndFormat(ref, ctx, opts)` |
| Format raw value as currency/date/boolean/number | `formatResolvedValue(raw, format, currencyCode)` |
| Get display name from insured snapshot | `getInsuredDisplayName(insured)` |
| Get insured type (personal/company) | `getInsuredType(insured)` |
| Get name from insured + packages fallback | `getDisplayNameFromSnapshot(snapshot)` |
| Case-insensitive key lookup on any object | `fuzzyGet(obj, key)` |
| Build formatted address from getter | `buildAddressFromGetter(getter)` |
| Get primary ID from insured snapshot | `getInsuredPrimaryId(insured)` |
| Get contact field (mobile, tel, email) | `getContactField(insured, key)` |
| Resolve document number for current template | `resolveRawValue({ source: "policy", fieldKey: "documentNumber" }, ctx)` — requires `documentTracking` + `currentDocTrackingKey` in ctx |

## NEVER duplicate these patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — inline insured name extraction
const last = snap.insured__lastName ?? snap.insured_lastName ?? snap.lastName;
const first = snap.insured__firstName ?? snap.insured_firstName ?? snap.firstName;
const name = [last, first].filter(Boolean).join(" ");

// ✅ GOOD
import { getInsuredDisplayName } from "@/lib/field-resolver";
const name = getInsuredDisplayName(insuredSnapshot);

// ❌ BAD — inline package value lookup with prefix fallback
const val = vals[key] ?? vals[`${pkg}__${key}`] ?? vals[`${pkg}_${key}`];

// ✅ GOOD
import { resolveRawValue } from "@/lib/field-resolver";
const val = resolveRawValue({ source: "package", fieldKey: key, packageName: pkg }, ctx);

// ❌ BAD — inline currency formatting
new Intl.NumberFormat("en-HK", { style: "currency", currency: "HKD" }).format(n);

// ✅ GOOD (for template/snapshot display)
import { formatResolvedValue } from "@/lib/field-resolver";
formatResolvedValue(n, "currency", "HKD");

// ✅ ALSO OK (for accounting UI — different concern)
import { fmtCurrency } from "@/lib/accounting-utils";
```

## Scope boundaries

- **Template/snapshot field resolution** → always use `lib/field-resolver.ts`
- **Accounting UI display** (cents → display) → use `lib/accounting-utils.ts` `fmtCurrency`
- **Live form values** (RHF) → use `lib/formula.ts` `resolveFieldValue` (different contract)
- **Date display in UI** → use `lib/format/date.ts` helpers
